A police officer was on Friday arrested for assaulting his boss. Wesley Cheti a police officer attached Kimanjo Police station situated in Laikipia North sub-county is reported to have attacked his OCS Joseph Kamitha. Cheti is said to have turned violent and started assaulting Kamitha after he was questioned why he had handcuffed two underage girls. The report at the police station says the reason Cheti had arrested the primary school girls is because they refused to give in into his sexual advances. "The reason behind the arrest of the two girls being , the girls denied him sex adverse that he requested them on August 5, " the police obstruct seen by the Star indicated. The OCS was questioning the officer on the matter when he attacked him, leaving him with bite injuries on the left breast among other places He was rushed to Kimanjo Sub-county hospital where he was treated and discharged.